			<content>[3 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] 25. Witt Library. Bird Trap Delporte
1) Delporte Flemish Exh. R.A. 1927, N° 224 14 3/4 x 22 cm (38 x 56 cm) (see Friedländer Apollo June 1927 with colour repr. Photograph of signature; 2) Doria Gall. Rome [...]; 3) Left half with bird trap as a complete picture, upright panel 34 x 28 cm Brummer Gallery, Paris 1910; 
[blad 1, verso]
4) Sale Muller, A'dam Nov. 1910, N° 18, Bois, 39 x 56 cm; 5) = ?4)? [sic] sale Heberle Coll. 29 May 1911, N° 12, Holz 33 x 68 (sic) probably 58; 6) Hessel Sale, Cercle Royale Antwerp, 29 May-2 June 1935, N° 77, Bois 39 x 56 (ex Vente L. van Walle, Anvers 1924, N° 119 bis; 7) Baron Coppée (poor photo) Bois 40 x 57,5; 8) Maguin Coll. (Sale?[sic]) Paris, N° 104, Bois 36,4 x57; 9) Cremer, Dortmund, Holz 26 x 43cm; 
[blad 2, recto] Witt Library. P.B.II 
A) Winter Landscape with Bird Trap: 1) Bruckenthal Coll. (Hermannstadt?[sic]) Eichenholz 56,5 x 39 cm; 2) Mayer van den Bergh Antwerp, N° 55, Panel 38,5 x 55 cm; 3) Fitzwilliam Mus. Cambridge, Copper 7 x 91/2 in.; 4) J.M. Chapman, California, Panel 15 x 22 in.; 5) Pardo Paris 160 Bd. Haussmann, 17 1/2 x 23in. Advert. in Burl.Mag. June 1952; 6) P. de Boer, A'dam 1935, dated 1604 (Advt. Figaro 1930, III Feb.; 
[blad 2, verso] 7) Rather coarse, [onleesbaar] Museum Sale, Am. Art Ass. N.Y. 27-28 March, 1930, N° 31, cradled panel 15 1/4 x 22in. ex coll. of Alexander Arensberg, Esq. London; 8) Slatter, London, Exh. 1944 (cutting from? [sic] Illustrated London News?[sic]); 9) Rome, Galleria Doria [...]; 10) Earl of Pembroke , Wilton House; 11) H. Haberfield, Vienna 1938, probalbly the same as Exh. [onleesbaar] 1925 from Private Coll. [onleesbaar], (cutting from Belvedere, Feb. March 1925; 12) Thomée Coll.Alkmaar, N° 103, Eichenholz 37,5 x 58,5 cm Vgl. auch Katal. Ausstell[un]g [onleesbaar]; 
[blad 3, recto] Witt Library. P.B.II Landscape with Bird Trap (continued)
13) Private Coll. Scotland, Panel 12 3/8 x 22 1/4 in. proportions of this and N°12 more horizontal than the others;
B) The same landscape, simplified and with the minor figures omitted. Sale Giroux, Brussels 12 Feb. 1949, N° 50, Bois 57 x 66 1/2 cm
C) Only the right half of the composition with the bird trap, Brummer Paris, 34 x 28 cm.</content>
